Definition: In this task, you are given concept set (with 3 to 5 concepts) that contain mentions of names of people, places, activities, or things. These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: lake#shore#walk
output:
output: boys walking on the shore beside lake

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: airport#passenger#plane
output:
output: A plane about to be boarded by passengers at airport

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: bedroom#decorate#style
output:
output: A small bedroom decorated in an antique style

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: clown#crowd#entertain
output:
output: a clown entertains a crowd

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: barn#eat#horse
output:
output: two horses eating grass close to a barn

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: blackboard#equation#write
output:
output: The man writing math equations on the blackboard.

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: bedroom#stripe#wall
output:
output: A bedroom has yellow curtains and yellow striped walls.

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: airplane#cargo#load
output:

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: couch#room#window
output:
output: this living room has two windows and a brown couch

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: park#train#yard
output:
output: A very old boxcar on an old train parked in a yard.

Now complete the following example-
input: bee#flower#pollinate

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: anchor#boat#island
output:
output: tourist boat anchored off the island

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: smoke#train#travel
output:
output: An antique train spewing black smoke as it travels.

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper

Now complete the following example-
input: bark#giraffe#tree
output:
output: Head of two giraffes with one slicking the bark on a tree.

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper

Now complete the following example-
input: feature#image#wear
output:

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: departure#station#train
output:
output: departure of the train from the station

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: city#cobble#street
output:
output: a city is a steep cobbled street as used in the famous adverts

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: bike#boat#park
output:
output: The bike is parked next to the boat.

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: lid#lift#toilet
output:
output: Someone who is lifting the lid to a small toilet.

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper

Now complete the following example-
input: planet#sun#system
output:
output: the sun and planets of our solar system .

Now complete the following example-
input: cluster#grape#vine
output:

Positive example 2-

Now complete the following example-

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: bee#fly#pollen
output:
output: many small bee are flying to collect pollen in the morning

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: give#politician#tour
output:
output: politician giving politician a tour

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: moon#planet#sun
output:
output: a planet and its moon are dimly lit by a distant sun

Now complete the following example-

output:

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper

Now complete the following example-
input: grass#park#van

Now complete the following example-

Now complete the following example-

Now complete the following example-

Positive example 2-

Now complete the following example-
input: cover#pizza#salad
output:

These concept sets reflect reasonable concept co-occurrences in everyday situations. All concepts given as input are separated by "#". Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: depart#passenger#station#train
output:
output: a passenger departs the train at station

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.

Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: gravy#meat#plate#vegetable
output:
output: a plate with a meat covered with gravy and vegetables

Your job is to generate a sentence describing a day-to-day scene using all concepts from a given concept set.
Positive example 1-
input: mountain#ski#skier
output: Skier skis down the mountain
Positive example 2-
input: call#character#contain#wallpaper
output: queen of wallpaper containing a portrait called film character .
Now complete the following example-
input: buy#home#money#save
output:
output: saving money to buy a new home of its own money in the piggy bank .
